@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{bibtex-completion-extras.el} provides a targeted extension for the
@samp{bibtex-completion} package, which underlies bibliography completion
interfaces such as @samp{ivy-bibtex} and @samp{helm-bibtex}.  It depends on
@samp{el-patch} for modifying the initialization function.

The sole purpose of this package is to disable the automatic file
watching that @samp{bibtex-completion} sets up during initialization.  By
default, @samp{bibtex-completion} uses @code{file-notify-add-watch} to monitor
bibliography files and automatically reload them when changes are
detected.  This can cause performance issues with large bibliography
files or on systems where file notification events are frequent.

By removing the file-watching code, this package trades automatic
reloading for manual control.  The bibliography data can still be
refreshed on demand by calling @code{bibtex-completion-clear-cache} followed
by any completion command, or simply by restarting Emacs.

